
# command to install pytest framework
->  pip install pytest

# In pytest in python with "test_" as prefix consider as test suite file

# In pytest file, function with "test_" as prefix will consider as test cases.

# command to execute pytest code in terminal
   ->  Open terminal in current location where the pytest file exist and run below command
  ->   python -m pytest -v -s .\test_basic_cases.py
   -m :  for current path a root location
   -v : verbose , it provides detailed
   -s :  console output of print statement


test_basic_cases.py::test_addition PASSED
test_basic_cases.py::test_multiplication PASSED
test_basic_cases.py::test_subtraction PASSED
test_basic_cases.py::test_division FAILED
test_basic_cases.py::test_greeting Welcome to Pytest
PASSED

======== 1 failed, 4 passed in 0.52s =====


# test class name has to be with capital T or Test as prefix of class

# function name should start with small letter test*<name>

# execute test cases with folder structure
  -> python -m pytest -v .\tests_practice\

# command to execute one specific test case.
   ->  python -m pytest -v -k "test_multiplication" .\tests_practice\smoke_class_marker_file.py
   -k :  pick specific test case.

# command to execute specific marker test cases in the file
   -> python -m pytest -v -m "smoke" .\tests_practice\smoke_class_marker_file.py


# command to exe3cute multiple matching marker with AND condition
  -> python -m pytest -v -m "smoke and sanity" .\tests_practice\smoke_class_marker_file.py

# command to exe3cute multiple matching marker with or condition
  -> python -m pytest -v -m "smoke or sanity" .\tests_practice\smoke_class_marker_file.py